# Dry-Run Install Documentation

Paired dry-run docs are **preparatory** (see `gxp-exec`): repeatable, `MODE: DRY-RUN` labelled, **never** generate deviations.

## Pairing requirement

- Every GxP Installation Procedure at `doc_install/eWise - Installation Procedure - <Component> - github.md` (excluding `dry_run/`) **must** have a matching dry-run doc at `doc_install/dry_run/eWise - Dry-Run Installation Procedure - <Component> - github.md`.
- Component names must match between paired files.

## Same-PR maintenance

When changing any of the following, **update the paired dry-run doc in the same PR** (or state in the PR description why not):

- Install, deploy, or publish GitHub workflow under `.github/workflows/`
- GxP Installation Procedure under `doc_install/`
- Install or publish script under `scripts/`

## Minimum detail (dry-run docs)

Every dry-run document **must** include:

- `MODE: DRY-RUN` banner at the top
- Link to the paired GxP Installation Procedure
- Full `workflow_dispatch` inputs table (name, type, default, required, description)
- **Pipeline Mirror**: one entry per workflow job and step (match source YAML)
- **Expected Actions**: per-step dry-run log pattern (e.g. `[dry-run] would ...`)
- **Mutation Guard**: table of systems that must not change during dry-run
- **Operator Verification Checklist**: numbered post-run checks

## Detail floor

- Do **not** remove step-level detail when the source workflow still contains that step.
- New workflow job or step → add matching rows in Pipeline Mirror, Expected Actions, and Mutation Guard if applicable.
- Dry-run docs are **more detailed** than GxP install procedures, not summaries of them.

## Skill to use

Use `dry-run-install-procedure` to create or refresh paired dry-run documentation.

## GxP boundary

- Dry-run documentation updates are **not** deviations.
- Deviations apply only to GxP **pre-requisites** and **run/install** phases (`gxp-exec`).
